I'm not sure the torrent is fake, but it's utterly useless because something is preventing the first and the last packet from being seeded, containing the non-video files and a chunk of the video.  Recently there was a torrent stuck at 99% with only the end of the video missing and that one could still be played, but this one I can't even repair using any of the MKV tools I know...

My guess is, someone who has the complete video file but not the text files inserted the video file and started leeching the torrent, thus seeding all the parts they had minus the parts containing files they didn't have.  And the person who made the torrent never even seeded it in the first place.  My suggestion would be to that person who has the video to make another torrent file without the text junk and seed that themselves. because this is helping nobody.

Or maybe the original seeder accidentally deleted the text files before they were finished seeding.  Either way, this sucks!
